  "text": "A standard brain MRI protocol for CV evaluation was followed, which included the following measurements [CITATION_1] : a) Spin-echo T1-and T2-weighted imaging, b) fluid-attenuated inversion recovery (FLAIR) imaging, c) diffusion-weighted (DW) imaging, d) susceptibility-weighted (SW) imaging, e) time-of-flight (TOF) MR angiography, and f) contrast-enhanced T1-weighted imaging (using fat sat suppression and flow compensation) and T1-weighted images (3 mm or less) of areas of abnormality on MRA/TOF.",
